# Cosmic Defenders Bookstore - Analytics Sandbox
### Overview
#### Online Bookstore Data
Imagine you're a local sci-fi and fantasy book seller. You've got the high-touch value of face-to-face, trusted , but you don't have the ability to scale as you like! So, you're adding an online catalogue to supplement your local inventory, with the ability for your customers to get direct recommendations, and buy directly from you rather than a "big box retailer". What do you need in order to make decisions on stock and inventory, demand, searches, trends, and metrics? That's right... analytics made easy, at your fingertips.

This is just a bit of dummy data that might be representative of a local offline-online bookstore. And while we're talking something small here, the point is to put yourself in the shoes of the business. We don't just need data, we need to turn that data into something useful. We're looking for answers to questions that will help our customers, and our own business, thrive. 
In our Cosmic Defenders bookstore, we will explore some typical questions every business user has at some point that might be relevant to what kind of titles we should buy, what our best sellers are, who our buyers are, and how to target them. 
Without analytics, we can't ask important questions like "How am I doing?", "What can be improved?" "who's my main buyer?" "who's my most loyal buyers?" "what's trending now?" "what am i running out of stock on, and thus losing selling opportunities on?" etc.
